1. The member has obtained the approval of the pledgee (the party who has provided the loan or credit);
2. The member has fulfilled all the conditions specified in the pledge agreement;
3. The member has completed all the procedures for the transfer of the pledged assets, including the submission of relevant documents and the payment of any fees or taxes.

In summary, a member can submit a report for the transfer of pledged assets when they have obtained the necessary approvals, fulfilled all the conditions specified in the pledge agreement, and completed all the relevant procedures.

